An Act relative to state police pensions.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 26 of Chapter 32 of the General Laws is hereby amended by striking paragraph
2 (c) and inserting the following:
3 (c) Upon retirement under the provisions of this subdivision, a member shall receive a
4 retirement allowance to become effective on the date of the member’s retirement. Payments
5 under such retirement allowance shall be made as provided for in sections twelve and thirteen
6 and the normal yearly amount thereof shall be equal to sixty percent of the average annual rate of
7 the member’s regular compensation during the twelve-month period of his creditable service
8 immediately preceding the date the member’s retirement allowance becomes effective; provided
9 further that the total amount of the allowance shall be increased by one-twelfth of three percent
10 for each full month of service in excess of twenty years of service and prior to the last day of the
